HEADWORD: Excandescent
<hw>Ex`can*des"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excandescens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>excandescere</ets> to take fire,
glow; <ets>ex</ets> out (intens.) + <ets>candescere</ets> to begin to
glisten or glow, fr. <ets>candere</ets>. See <er>Candid</er>.]</ety>
<def>White or glowing with heat.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

